        <h1>Microwave Not Heating</h1>
        <img src="../../../assets/images/pictures/microwave.jpg" alt="Microwave" style="width:400px; margin:20px 0;">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>If your microwave is not heating food, it might be a faulty magnetron, fuse, or door switch. This guide helps identify the problem safely.</p>
        <h2>Tools Needed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Screwdriver</li>
            <li>Multimeter</li>
            <li>Replacement fuse or magnetron</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Unplug the microwave before any inspection.</li>
            <li>Check the fuse with a multimeter; replace if blown.</li>
            <li>Inspect the door switch; replace if faulty.</li>
            <li>If the magnetron is defective, replace it carefully.</li>
            <li>Test the microwave with a small cup of water to ensure it heats.</li>
        </ol>
        <h2>Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Never operate with the cover removed.</li>
            <li>Use caution when handling high-voltage components.</li>
        </ul>
